14. Qf3 Kh7 $6 (14... c4 $1) 15. Be3 $6 b6 (15... d4 $1) 16. Rad1 $6 d4 $17 {
and Black went on to win, but startiing from move 14 and on the next two moves
McShane could successfully fight for an advantage by jumping to g4.}) 12...
dxe4 {Black relieves tension in the center, a reasonable alternative is} (12...
Re8 13. Ba4 Nd7 14. Qc1 Kh7 15. h4 d4 16. h5 Rc8 17. c4 Qe7 18. hxg6+ fxg6 $132
) 13. dxe4 Qe7 {A good square for the queen.} 14. Bxe6 Qxe6 15. Be3 b6 16. Qa4
