d4 Bxb1 13. dxc5 {can still transpose to the main line}) 9... Be7 10. d4 cxd4
11. cxd4 O-O 12. Nbd2 {Black has successfully developed and can show activity
on the queenside in an original way -} bxa4 $5 13. Rxa4 a5 $1 {(securing a
nice outpost on b4)} 14. Ra1 Nb8 $5 {(improving the knight)} 15. e5 dxe5 16.
dxe5 Nd5 17. Nc4 Nc6 $132) 8... axb5 9. Rxa8 Qxa8 10. Bxb5 Bxe4 {Usually the
central pawn is more valuable than the flank one. But here White is relying on
a speedy development. and organizing an attack until the enemy king is still
exposed to danger in the center.} 11. d4 $5 {An interesting piece sacrifice
and a clear sign that White is a not going to count the material. This
continuation has already been discussed in practical games.} ({The alternative
} 11. Na3 {is harmless -} e6 12. d4 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Qxf3 14. gxf3 cxd4 15. cxd4
Be7 16. Bf4 O-O $11) 11... Bxb1 $5 {Black must take the knight, otherwise
White's initiative will be for free.} 12. dxc5 Be4 $1 {The strongest move. The
